    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq identifies three root causes of disbelief (kufr): greed, arrogance, and envy, each illustrated with a primordial example from sacred history. Adam's greed led him to eat from the forbidden tree, Iblis's arrogance made him refuse to prostrate before Adam, and Cain's envy drove him to murder his brother Abel. These three vices are thus presented as the foundational spiritual diseases from which all forms of disbelief originate.",
        "key_terms": {
          "أصول الكفر": "Usul al-Kufr - the foundations or roots of disbelief; the fundamental spiritual vices that underlie all forms of rejection of God",
          "الحرص": "al-Hirs - greed, covetousness; the insatiable desire for what one does not have",
          "الاستكبار": "al-Istikbar - arrogance, self-aggrandizement; considering oneself above others or above God's commands",
          "الحسد": "al-Hasad - envy; wishing for the removal of blessings from others"
        },
        "seo_question": "What are the three foundations of disbelief according to Imam al-Sadiq?"
